This is the same scenario as when they were publicly demanding the Taliban hand over Bin Ladin, they never really wanted the Taliban to hand him over, as that was their justification for invading Afghanistan enabling them to destroy both bin Ladin and destroy the Taliban. If the Taliban had handed over bin Ladin, and carried out all US demands they would most likely still be in power ..... Saddam aint so dumb and cares only for himself rather than idology, he knows he can increase his chances of survival by pandering to the UN over the next few months. support for any US action has already crumbled since iraq agreed to let inspectors back in. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uxaenneax.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xaen Neax</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 517<br> <font color=#333333>(9/17/02 8:38:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fnamelesstavernfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=929.topic&index=172>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://webpages.charter.net/philipv1/small.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: .</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  <br>
